HEADWORD: Seersucker
<hw>Seer"suck`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A light fabric,
originally made in the East Indies, of silk and linen, usually having
alternating stripes, and a slightly craped or puckered surface; also, a
cotton fabric of similar appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

